<subSubSection id="25D825820E31FFA63C0BFEF7FA88E1E3" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="6D7D76090E31FFA63C0BFEF7FA88E1E3" blockId="6.[839,1482,351,950]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">
<emphasis id="5FB6AA1B0E31FFA63C0BFEF7FC73E323" bold="true" box="[839,957,351,374]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The combination of the presence of a dorsal fin with an ossified spinelet and the presence of pectoral- and dorsal-fin spines distinguishes the species of 
<taxonomicName id="AAC20D8A0E31FFA63A0DFE36FA07E3E3" authorityName="Vari &amp; Ferraris Jr &amp; de Pinna" authorityYear="2005" box="[1345,1481,414,438]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cetopsidae" genus="Cetopsidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5FB6AA1B0E31FFA63A0DFE36FA07E3E3" box="[1345,1481,414,438]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">Cetopsidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from all other genera in the 
<taxonomicName id="AAC20D8A0E31FFA63B3DFE17FB22E383" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1858" box="[1137,1260,447,470]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cetopsidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Cetopsinae">Cetopsinae</taxonomicName>
. The possession of a lateral line extending to over the posterior portion of the base of the anal fin but falling short of the caudal peduncle is also unique to 
<taxonomicName id="AAC20D8A0E31FFA63CE3FDB6FBF9E063" authorityName="Vari &amp; Ferraris Jr &amp; de Pinna" authorityYear="2005" box="[943,1079,542,566]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cetopsidae" genus="Cetopsidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5FB6AA1B0E31FFA63CE3FDB6FBF9E063" box="[943,1079,542,566]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">Cetopsidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within the 
<taxonomicName id="AAC20D8A0E31FFA63BE7FDB7FAE8E063" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1858" box="[1195,1318,543,566]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cetopsidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Cetopsinae">Cetopsinae</taxonomicName>
. The other genera within the 
<taxonomicName id="AAC20D8A0E31FFA63CA4FD97FBAEE003" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1858" box="[1000,1120,575,598]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cetopsidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Cetopsinae">Cetopsinae</taxonomicName>
either have a shorter lateral line that is restricted to the abdominal portion of the body (
<taxonomicName id="AAC20D8A0E31FFA63C1CFD28FBF6E0C2" authorityName="Ferraris" authorityYear="1996" box="[848,1080,640,663]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cetopsidae" genus="Denticetopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="royeroi">
<emphasis id="5FB6AA1B0E31FFA63C1CFD28FBF6E0C2" box="[848,1080,640,663]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">Denticetopsis royeroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="AAC20D8A0E31FFA63B21FD28FB0FE0C3" authorityName="Ferraris" authorityYear="1996" box="[1133,1217,638,663]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cetopsidae" genus="Denticetopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sauli">
<emphasis id="5FB6AA1B0E31FFA63B21FD28FB0FE0C3" box="[1133,1217,638,663]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">D. sauli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or have a longer lateral line extending posteriorly at least onto the posterior portion of the caudal peduncle (all members of the 
<taxonomicName id="AAC20D8A0E31FFA63A57FD17FA5DE083" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1858" box="[1307,1427,703,726]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cetopsidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Cetopsinae">Cetopsinae</taxonomicName>
with the exception of 
<taxonomicName id="AAC20D8A0E31FFA63CB1FD48FB28E0A2" authorityName="Ferraris" authorityYear="1996" box="[1021,1254,736,759]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cetopsidae" genus="Denticetopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="royeroi">
<emphasis id="5FB6AA1B0E31FFA63CB1FD48FB28E0A2" box="[1021,1254,736,759]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">Denticetopsis royeroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="AAC20D8A0E31FFA63A51FD48FABCE0A3" authorityName="Ferraris" authorityYear="1996" box="[1309,1394,734,759]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cetopsidae" genus="Denticetopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sauli">
<emphasis id="5FB6AA1B0E31FFA63A51FD48FABCE0A3" box="[1309,1394,734,759]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">D. sauli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the species of 
<taxonomicName id="AAC20D8A0E31FFA63CFFFD56FBF7E143" authorityName="Vari &amp; Ferraris Jr &amp; de Pinna" authorityYear="2005" box="[947,1081,766,790]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cetopsidae" genus="Cetopsidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5FB6AA1B0E31FFA63CFFFD56FBF7E143" box="[947,1081,766,790]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">Cetopsidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName id="AAC20D8A0E31FFA63B01FD56FB1DE143" authorityName="Vari &amp; Ferraris Jr &amp; de Pinna" authorityYear="2005" box="[1101,1235,766,790]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cetopsidae" genus="Cetopsidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5FB6AA1B0E31FFA63B01FD56FB1DE143" box="[1101,1235,766,790]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">Cetopsidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is further distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="AAC20D8A0E31FFA63CCEFC88FBDBE162" authorityName="Ferraris" authorityYear="1996" box="[898,1045,800,823]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cetopsidae" genus="Denticetopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5FB6AA1B0E31FFA63CCEFC88FBDBE162" box="[898,1045,800,823]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">Denticetopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the mental barbels extending posteriorly beyond the rear margin of the opercle 
<emphasis id="5FB6AA1B0E31FFA63A1EFCE8FA59E102" box="[1362,1431,832,855]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">versus</emphasis>
falling short of that point, respectively, and in having a deeplyforked caudal-fin margin in contrast to an emarginate or obliquely-truncate caudal-fin margin, respectively.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="25D825820E31FFA63C0BFC77FAFBE603" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="6D7D76090E31FFA63C0BFC77FAFBE603" blockId="6.[839,1482,990,1110]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">
<emphasis id="5FB6AA1B0E31FFA63C0BFC77FC06E1A3" bold="true" box="[839,968,991,1014]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">Etymology.</emphasis>
The genus name, 
<taxonomicName id="AAC20D8A0E31FFA63BDEFC76FAD4E1A3" authorityName="Vari &amp; Ferraris Jr &amp; de Pinna" authorityYear="2005" box="[1170,1306,990,1014]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cetopsidae" genus="Cetopsidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5FB6AA1B0E31FFA63BDEFC76FAD4E1A3" box="[1170,1306,990,1014]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">Cetopsidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<taxonomicName id="AAC20D8A0E31FFA63A29FC77FA0CE1A3" box="[1381,1474,991,1014]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cetopsidae" genus="Cetopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5FB6AA1B0E31FFA63A29FC77FA0CE1A3" box="[1381,1474,991,1014]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">Cetopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, that was the first genus proposed in the 
<taxonomicName id="AAC20D8A0E31FFA63A5BFC57FA5AE643" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1858" box="[1303,1428,1023,1046]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cetopsidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Cetopsinae">Cetopsinae</taxonomicName>
, and “idium” meaning diminutive, is in reference to the relatively small body sizes of the members of the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
